# Soul Elements - Project Context

## Overview
BaZi (Chinese Four Pillars) fortune-telling web app. Dark-themed, all English content.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js (app directory), React, CSS
- **Backend**: Express.js (Node.js)
- **Database**: Neon PostgreSQL
- **PDF**: PDFKit (server-side)
- **Hosting**: Railway (stemssouls.up.railway.app)
- **Payments**: Stripe

## Design System
- Background: #07080A
- Gold accent: #C9A84C
- Blue accent: #3B82F6
- Font size: text-base minimum for body text
- Tai Chi background image (bg-design.jpg, opacity ~0.2-0.25)

## Project Structure
```
soul-elements/
  frontend/        # Next.js app
    src/app/
      page.js              - Homepage
      input/page.js        - Birth info input form
      preview/page.js      - Report preview before purchase
      report/page.js       - Full report with PDF download
      success/page.js      - Stripe payment success
      components/
        ElementRadarChart.js    - Element chart
        FortuneStickOracle.js   - 60 sticks oracle
      globals.css         - Global styles
      layout.js           - Root layout
    public/
      bg-design.jpg       - Background image
      data/sixtySticks.json

  backend/         # Express.js server
    server.js
    routes/         - API routes (analyze, report, geocode, stripe, webhook)
    lib/
      baziEngine.js       - BaZi calculation engine
      advancedCalculations.js
      reportContent.js    - Report content builder
      translationMap.js   - English translations
      core/               - soul-elements-core library
        tst.js            - True Solar Time (Meeus algorithm)
        dayun.js          - DaYun calculation (jieqi-based)
        elements.js       - Element scoring
      pdf/
        pdfGenerator.js   - PDFKit generation (34pg Standard / 46pg Grand Master)
```

## Pages Flow
Homepage -> Input (birth date/time/location) -> Preview -> Purchase (Stripe) -> Report + PDF Download

## Key Conventions
- All English content (no Chinese characters)
- Keep text-base minimum font sizes
- Maintain dark theme with gold/blue accents
- BG image visible at ~0.2-0.25 opacity
- Match Dante Calculator Pro style (blue #3498DB accent, dark #0D1117 bg) as reference

## Important Notes
- Frontend uses Next.js app router
- PDF generation is server-side (PDFKit), not browser print
- Location uses Nominatim geocoding (Nominatim is just for city/country; timezone uses grouped UTC modal picker)
- Email delivery is skipped for v1 (Stripe auto-receipt)
